						<summary>

						<p>Stone at a distance of a furlong from the shrine of Āñjaneya.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Śrī Rangarāya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1496, Bhāva, Jyēshṭa, śu. 15,</hi> corresponding to 1574 A.D., June 18, Friday.</p>						

						<p>Slightly damaged. It mentions a gift of land as <hi rend="italic">dasavanda</hi> for having repaired a breach in the local tank and also mentions Narasiṁharājaya of Nandyāla.</p>						

						</summary>
